Apply
SaveJob Responsibilities：

Be the FP&A of regional non-smartphone and smartphone in non-significant markets in SEA (like Myanmar, Laos), report to regional FP&A manager directly;

Conduct financial analysis to evaluate financial performance, identify trends, and provide insights to support decision-making. This includes analyzing key financial metrics, variance analysis, profitability analysis, and conducting scenario analysis to assess the impact of different business strategies;

Collaborate closely with business departments to monitor and manage the budget and usage of expenses like sales rebate, maketing and retail expenses;

Understand different nature of expense in the non-smartphone GTM departments and driving efficiencies.




Job requirement：

Bachelor’s degree (or above) in finance, accounting or similar majors;

Above at least 5 years working experience;

Ability to positively and effectively interact with senior business stakeholders;

Advanced knowledge of MS Excel, with ability to learn new software/tools with minimal supervision;

Excellent knowledge and understanding of financial and management accounting, process and systems. Experience in a comparable industry is a plus;

Fluent in English and Chinese;

